"Rapa" means "flash" in Polynesian. Rapa Iti is part of the Bass Islands in French Polynesia. Easter Island is called Rapa Nui because of its resemblance to it. Rapamycin is named after Rapa Nui because it was isolated there. The mTOR receptor means "mammal target of Rapamycin".

"Mammal" is supposedly from Dr. C. Linnaeus, "of the breast". And the "-mycin" means it's derived from fungi. Thus mTOR means "target for flash-out-of-fungi for those of the breast". Scientific sounding names obscure the true brutality of their own etymology.
